{
  "texts": [
    "His daily medications included atorvastatin 40 mg, hydrochlorothiazide 12.5 mg, and lisinopril 40 mg. His diabetes was diet-controlled.",
    "His past ocular history included a branch retinal vein occlusion in the right eye four years prior and a right sixth nerve palsy two years prior with spontaneous resolution of diplopia after 10 weeks.",
    "He did not smoke or consume alcohol.",
    "He worked as an automobile mechanic.",
    "On examination, BCVA was 20/20 in both eyes."
  ]
}